To create a kexec-loader bootdisk:

1) Edit the CC variable in Makefile to the correct gcc
2) Create or download a static kexec binary
3) Use mkinitramfs.sh to create a Linux initramfs CPIO archive
4) Compile a Linux kernel with the required drivers and initramfs image
5) Copy the kernel and a bootloader such as Syslinux to a floppy
